glosses: causative of aşmak: to make exceed
to pass something over, especially through a place where it is difficult to cross or pass over something
to sneak past, sneak through, to secretly get through

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish آشیرمق (aşırmak), آشرمق (aşurmak), from Old Anatolian Turkish اشرمق (aşurmaq), from Proto-Common Turkic *āšur-, a derivation from Proto-Common Turkic *āš-. By surface analysis, aş- (“to exceed”) + -ır (“causative suffix”). Cognate with Chagatai اشورماق (ašurmaq).
